content:
Use the Knowledge One widget to find articles that help solve customer issues during chats.

Available in: Salesforce Classic, Performance Editions and Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Unlimited Edition and Enterprise Edition with Service Cloud.

To search for and view an article: Read on the article type.

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026.

The Knowledge One widget is only available if your Salesforce org uses Salesforce Knowledge and your admin has included the tool in your app.

When chatting with a visitor, click an article from the list in the Knowledge One widget. A tab with the full text of the article opens.

To search for a specific article, type a word or phrase in the text box and click .

When you find the article, click , then click Share.

The text of the article appears in the chat text box. To send it to the visitor, click Send.

You can send articles only if your admin has set up a Chat Answer field on articles.

Set Up Chat Answers from Knowledge Articles
title: Attach Articles to Chats in Service Cloud
